::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:01.520 --> 00:00:03.650
Wealth, fame, power...

3
00:00:03.650 --> 00:00:07.820
Gold Roger, the King of the Pirates, obtained everything the world has to offer.

4
00:00:07.820 --> 00:00:11.660
What he said in his final moments drove countless souls to the seas.

5
00:00:11.660 --> 00:00:13.660
You want my treasure?

6
00:00:13.660 --> 00:00:15.450
Go ahead.

7
00:00:15.450 --> 00:00:16.660
Find it!

8
00:00:16.660 --> 00:00:19.250
Everything is right where I left it!

9
00:00:21.670 --> 00:00:26.380
People set their sights on the Grand Line in pursuit of their dreams.

10
00:00:26.380 --> 00:00:29.630
The world has truly entered the Great Pirate Era!

11
00:00:30.390 --> 00:00:35.640
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

12
00:00:30.470 --> 00:00:35.640
Arittake no yume wo kaki atsume

13
00:00:35.850 --> 00:00:41.440
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for
Sagashi mono wo sagashi ni yuku no sa

14
00:00:41.770 --> 00:00:42.690
One Piece!
ONE PIECE

15
00:00:47.900 --> 00:00:52.700
Compasses? Not for me. Left them all behind
Rashinban nante juutai no moto

16
00:00:53.580 --> 00:00:58.500
I'm headed out to sea, with my heart serving as guide
Netsu ni ukasare kaji wo toru no sa

17
00:00:59.330 --> 00:01:04.540
Following the ancient map to the spot marked "X" reveals
Hokori kabutteta takara no chizu mo

18
00:01:04.540 --> 00:01:09.760
Yeah, it's only legendary till someone proves it's real
Tashikameta no nara densetsu janai!

19
00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:13.710
When the world's got you down,

20
00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:16.850
Kojin teki na arashi wa dare ka no

21
00:01:13.710 --> 00:01:16.850
lean on your crew, they'll turn it around

22
00:01:17.180 --> 00:01:22.190
Their biorhythm will carry you through
BIORHYTHM nokkatte

23
00:01:22.400 --> 00:01:24.230
We're gonna make the most of it
Omoi sugoseba ii!

24
00:01:26.110 --> 00:01:31.400
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams
Arittake no yume wo kaki atsume

25
00:01:31.610 --> 00:01:36.990
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for
Sagashi mono wo sagashi ni yuku no sa

26
00:01:37.330 --> 00:01:40.040
Got some change to my name,
POCKET no COIN

27
00:01:40.040 --> 00:01:43.250
and maybe you wanna be my friend?
Soreto YOU WANNA BE MY FRIEND?

28
00:01:43.540 --> 00:01:48.130
We are, we are on the cruise!
WE ARE, WE ARE ON THE CRUISE!

29
00:01:48.920 --> 00:01:49.760
WE ARE!

30
00:01:50.010 --> 00:01:51.470
Hey, lackey!

31
00:01:50.050 --> 00:01:55.350
The Stalwart War Spear

32
00:01:51.470 --> 00:01:52.510
Hang in there!

33
00:01:52.510 --> 00:01:53.760
Now, breathe!

34
00:01:53.760 --> 00:01:55.510
Breathe in lots of good air!

35
00:01:55.510 --> 00:01:57.760
Are you all right? Hey!

36
00:01:57.760 --> 00:02:00.140
How about some water? Hey!

37
00:02:01.810 --> 00:02:03.190
This is bad.

38
00:02:03.190 --> 00:02:05.440
Do you wanna eat
my special pudding?

39
00:02:05.440 --> 00:02:06.150
It's good!

40
00:02:06.150 --> 00:02:09.570
Idiot! You wanna feed poison
to a poisoned man?!

41
00:02:09.570 --> 00:02:11.280
Hey, what do you mean by poison?!

42
00:02:11.280 --> 00:02:13.070
You're one to talk!

43
00:02:13.070 --> 00:02:14.070
What'd you say?!

44
00:02:14.070 --> 00:02:16.700
People say my meat dishes
are the best in the world!

45
00:02:16.700 --> 00:02:19.240
They're good enough to die for!

46
00:02:19.870 --> 00:02:21.120
Don't die on us!

47
00:02:23.870 --> 00:02:26.750
H-How's this fight gonna turn out?

48
00:02:26.750 --> 00:02:28.840
Idiot! That was just dumb luck!

49
00:02:28.840 --> 00:02:31.840
A stupid brat could
never defeat the don!

50
00:02:31.840 --> 00:02:33.220
Don't worry!

51
00:02:33.220 --> 00:02:34.630
Cabin Boy...

52
00:02:36.300 --> 00:02:41.270
"I'm not gonna die here"... you say?

53
00:02:44.270 --> 00:02:47.690
If you won't die here...

54
00:02:47.690 --> 00:02:49.650
then...

55
00:02:50.230 --> 00:02:52.690
who the hell will?!

56
00:02:54.150 --> 00:02:55.660
It'll be you, of course!

57
00:02:57.370 --> 00:02:59.370
No, it'll be you!

58
00:03:03.410 --> 00:03:05.420
The don was knocked down again!

59
00:03:05.420 --> 00:03:08.000
What the hell is going on?!

60
00:03:08.540 --> 00:03:14.510
O-Our enemies usually die
before even touching Don Krieg...

61
00:03:14.970 --> 00:03:17.300
He's supposed to be invincible...

62
00:03:17.300 --> 00:03:18.390
What the...

63
00:03:20.220 --> 00:03:22.390
What the hell is that brat?!

64
00:03:24.560 --> 00:03:26.980
He's really good!

65
00:03:26.980 --> 00:03:29.520
Yeah, I'm blown away...

66
00:03:29.520 --> 00:03:30.770
He's amazing!

67
00:03:30.770 --> 00:03:32.360
Get that Krieg bastard!

68
00:03:32.360 --> 00:03:34.690
Yeah, he can do it!

69
00:03:34.690 --> 00:03:38.070
That brat is actually going
toe to toe with the don...

70
00:03:38.070 --> 00:03:41.240
Is this a dream? The don's getting
beat by someone like him...

71
00:03:41.240 --> 00:03:43.080
The don's supposed to be invincible...

72
00:03:43.080 --> 00:03:46.210
Don Krieg's legend as
the greatest is about to be...

73
00:03:46.210 --> 00:03:48.670
Stop spouting nonsense!

74
00:03:56.840 --> 00:03:58.090
What the...

75
00:03:59.050 --> 00:04:01.350
F-Finally...

76
00:04:01.350 --> 00:04:03.560
Don Krieg's ultimate weapon...

77
00:04:03.560 --> 00:04:05.060
The Stalwart War Spear!

78
00:04:06.230 --> 00:04:07.480
What's that?

79
00:04:07.480 --> 00:04:08.730
It exploded.

80
00:04:09.150 --> 00:04:10.650
Now...

81
00:04:10.650 --> 00:04:13.400
Let's see how long
you can run from this.

82
00:04:13.400 --> 00:04:16.280
It'll be a sight, anchor boy.

83
00:04:16.650 --> 00:04:21.030
While you may still be standing after
a few hits from those puny stakes,

84
00:04:21.030 --> 00:04:24.740
the Stalwart Spear is different.

85
00:04:25.540 --> 00:04:27.750
A single touch will blow you to bits!

86
00:04:30.420 --> 00:04:32.380
Wh-What's with that spear?!

87
00:04:33.840 --> 00:04:35.800
Don't fall, don't fall!

88
00:04:36.300 --> 00:04:38.130
Wh-What's with that spear?

89
00:04:38.130 --> 00:04:40.760
There's an explosion with every hit?

90
00:04:42.350 --> 00:04:44.470
What? My knees...

91
00:04:46.560 --> 00:04:48.810
It'll be a problem if this fight drags on.

92
00:04:48.810 --> 00:04:50.440
He's lost too much blood.

93
00:04:50.850 --> 00:04:52.520
He won't last much longer...

94
00:04:52.520 --> 00:04:55.020
Your overexertion has
taken its toll on you.

95
00:04:55.020 --> 00:04:58.490
You must be reaching your limit.

96
00:04:58.490 --> 00:04:59.990
Dammit...

97
00:04:59.990 --> 00:05:03.490
With the way it's rocking,
I can't go all out.

98
00:05:03.490 --> 00:05:04.990
I'm stumped.

99
00:05:04.990 --> 00:05:09.250
The Stalwart War Spear
never ceases to amaze me.

100
00:05:09.830 --> 00:05:14.090
Yeah, the harder you slam
that big spear down,

101
00:05:14.090 --> 00:05:16.340
the bigger the explosion it causes.

102
00:05:16.340 --> 00:05:19.670
It's a weapon that only
the don could possibly handle!

103
00:05:25.890 --> 00:05:28.890
He's so powerful...

104
00:05:28.890 --> 00:05:31.520
He's swinging around that
heavy spear so easily...

105
00:05:31.520 --> 00:05:35.520
With those shoulder guards,
it's gotta weigh at least a ton!

106
00:05:35.940 --> 00:05:39.610
That strength is exactly why
nobody can match the don!

107
00:05:46.990 --> 00:05:47.950
Take this!

108
00:05:51.960 --> 00:05:53.250
Die!

109
00:05:54.210 --> 00:05:55.170
Cabin Boy!

110
00:05:58.630 --> 00:05:59.840
That was close.

111
00:06:03.430 --> 00:06:05.050
You...

112
00:06:05.050 --> 00:06:07.140
damn insect!

113
00:06:17.610 --> 00:06:18.820
Cabin Boy!

114
00:06:33.080 --> 00:06:34.540
Cabin Boy...

115
00:06:36.210 --> 00:06:37.590
I'm not done yet.

116
00:06:37.590 --> 00:06:40.050
You've pissed me off.

117
00:06:40.050 --> 00:06:42.260
I won't let you die so easily.

118
00:06:42.590 --> 00:06:43.760
Dammit!

119
00:06:43.760 --> 00:06:47.260
That Krieg bastard pulls out
weapons one after another...

120
00:06:47.260 --> 00:06:49.220
There's no way that cabin boy can...

121
00:06:49.220 --> 00:06:52.850
Even if you pierce his body
with hundreds of weapons,

122
00:06:52.850 --> 00:06:57.150
nobody stands a chance against
a spear of blind determination.

123
00:07:14.080 --> 00:07:15.160
How easy...

124
00:07:25.630 --> 00:07:28.140
Now that makes you worth crushing.

125
00:07:36.480 --> 00:07:39.190
Life or death...

126
00:07:39.190 --> 00:07:45.110
In a battle between pirates, you'll fall apart
if you fear death for even a moment.

127
00:07:45.110 --> 00:07:46.700
What are you talking about?

128
00:07:46.700 --> 00:07:48.320
At least...

129
00:07:59.170 --> 00:08:00.920
At least...

130
00:08:04.300 --> 00:08:06.380
that kid isn't showing...

131
00:08:07.010 --> 00:08:09.340
the smallest amount of hesitation!

132
00:08:21.900 --> 00:08:24.820
Is it a survival instinct?

133
00:08:27.150 --> 00:08:29.950
Or does he not fear death
due to his conviction?

134
00:08:32.990 --> 00:08:34.580
Conviction...

135
00:08:45.880 --> 00:08:50.090
Y-You son of a bitch!

136
00:08:55.350 --> 00:08:56.600
Alright! You're amazing!

137
00:08:56.600 --> 00:08:58.930
Cabin Boy! Go for it!

138
00:08:57.520 --> 00:08:58.930
Get him!

139
00:09:01.560 --> 00:09:03.110
I told you...

140
00:09:03.480 --> 00:09:05.860
that this is where you die!

141
00:09:09.700 --> 00:09:13.780
I stand unparalleled!

142
00:09:19.750 --> 00:09:23.580
The fleet that Krieg gathered...
His hundreds of weapons and poisons...

143
00:09:23.580 --> 00:09:26.210
If that's what power is...

144
00:09:30.340 --> 00:09:32.890
then that kid's spear...

145
00:09:32.890 --> 00:09:35.350
is power as well.

146
00:09:36.760 --> 00:09:39.680
The spear held in his heart.

147
00:09:40.850 --> 00:09:47.570
I know an idiot who holds that
spear back for no good reason.

148
00:09:57.620 --> 00:09:59.330
M-My Stalwart War Spear...

149
00:09:59.830 --> 00:10:01.660
What the hell did you do?!

150
00:10:09.170 --> 00:10:11.630
I punched it five times.

151
00:10:12.420 --> 00:10:15.260
I guess that's it for your spear.

152
00:10:18.720 --> 00:10:20.350
Get ready...

153
00:10:24.060 --> 00:10:26.480
I have enough room now
to kick your ass!

154
00:10:27.980 --> 00:10:28.940
What?

155
00:10:28.940 --> 00:10:33.400
With the blade broken,
that spear's just a bomb on a stick.

156
00:10:33.400 --> 00:10:35.030
It's only half as strong.

157
00:10:35.030 --> 00:10:36.570
You think so?

158
00:10:36.570 --> 00:10:37.530
Yeah, I do.

159
00:10:38.910 --> 00:10:40.120
A bomb on a stick?

160
00:10:40.120 --> 00:10:41.750
Sounds good to me.

161
00:10:41.750 --> 00:10:46.130
Given the shape you're in, it's more
than enough to blow you away.

162
00:10:46.790 --> 00:10:51.710
With your body falling apart like that,
anything you say just sounds like a bluff.

163
00:10:52.090 --> 00:10:53.420
I'm not bluffing.

164
00:10:55.510 --> 00:10:57.550
That kid is pretty good.

165
00:10:57.550 --> 00:10:59.430
He just might pull it off!

166
00:11:00.260 --> 00:11:02.060
This is bad...

167
00:11:02.060 --> 00:11:04.390
How did he break
the Stalwart War Spear...?

168
00:11:09.900 --> 00:11:13.280
But he's taken so many explosions...

169
00:11:13.280 --> 00:11:14.860
His body can't keep up.

170
00:11:17.110 --> 00:11:18.620
Just give it up!

171
00:11:18.620 --> 00:11:21.830
The moment you defied Don Krieg,

172
00:11:22.950 --> 00:11:25.250
you signed your death warrant!

173
00:11:25.250 --> 00:11:26.120
I won't die!

174
00:11:31.250 --> 00:11:32.880
Hey! I'm over here!

175
00:11:32.880 --> 00:11:34.010
That monkey!

176
00:11:42.010 --> 00:11:43.430
He keeps swinging around!

177
00:11:48.810 --> 00:11:49.980
It's useless!

178
00:11:53.820 --> 00:11:56.030
Just how many weapons
does he have in there?!

179
00:12:06.040 --> 00:12:07.870
Gum-Gum...

180
00:12:08.250 --> 00:12:10.000
Gatling!

181
00:12:22.640 --> 00:12:23.680
Weak!

182
00:12:24.390 --> 00:12:28.890
Your punches are powerless
against this wootz steel armor!

183
00:12:28.890 --> 00:12:31.810
You can't even put a dent in it.

184
00:12:34.730 --> 00:12:36.650
Gum-Gum Pistol!

185
00:12:46.540 --> 00:12:48.040
Don!

186
00:12:49.750 --> 00:12:51.580
How impudent!

187
00:12:57.510 --> 00:13:01.010
Useless! Useless! Utterly useless!

188
00:13:01.010 --> 00:13:06.600
This armor won't break, even with
hundreds of monkey punches!

189
00:13:08.060 --> 00:13:10.940
I think I'm pretty close...

190
00:13:13.860 --> 00:13:15.070
He's gone...

191
00:13:15.070 --> 00:13:16.570
I'm right here!

192
00:13:21.610 --> 00:13:22.610
Listen up.

193
00:13:22.610 --> 00:13:27.830
Ultimate power is the result of advanced
equipment wielded by the most strength.

194
00:13:28.830 --> 00:13:31.830
The strong will always prevail.

195
00:13:31.830 --> 00:13:33.790
The strong!

196
00:13:37.050 --> 00:13:38.630
Then, that'd be me!

197
00:13:38.630 --> 00:13:43.760
Gum-Gum...

198
00:13:41.340 --> 00:13:43.760
Useless! Useless! It's useless!

199
00:13:43.760 --> 00:13:47.390
Stubbornness will only get you so far!

200
00:13:51.100 --> 00:13:53.730
Bazooka!

201
00:14:03.280 --> 00:14:04.570
No good!

202
00:14:04.570 --> 00:14:07.200
This is all you can do!

203
00:14:10.580 --> 00:14:13.830
What?! My invincible armor is cracking?!

204
00:14:16.790 --> 00:14:18.170
But it's too late.

205
00:14:18.920 --> 00:14:22.720
You're done for, anchor boy!

206
00:14:26.430 --> 00:14:28.390
It's a trap! Run!

207
00:14:38.070 --> 00:14:39.730
Cabin Boy!

208
00:14:56.920 --> 00:14:59.630
Is it a survival instinct?

209
00:15:00.000 --> 00:15:02.710
Or does he not fear death
due to his conviction?

210
00:15:06.550 --> 00:15:08.550
Gum-Gum...

211
00:15:08.550 --> 00:15:10.060
What?!

212
00:15:12.930 --> 00:15:15.980
Bazooka!

213
00:15:41.880 --> 00:15:43.010
All right!

214
00:15:42.170 --> 00:15:43.010
Good job!

215
00:15:43.010 --> 00:15:44.800
You're the best, Cabin Boy!

216
00:15:47.130 --> 00:15:49.260
I win!

217
00:15:53.220 --> 00:15:55.100
Don't get carried away, brat!

218
00:15:55.680 --> 00:15:56.560
He's still alive!

219
00:15:59.560 --> 00:16:00.190
Uh oh!

220
00:16:05.110 --> 00:16:08.280
Let's see you escape this steel net!

221
00:16:19.120 --> 00:16:20.630
Below us is the ocean!

222
00:16:20.630 --> 00:16:23.130
It's over, anchor boy!

223
00:16:23.130 --> 00:16:26.670
The last laugh belongs to me!

224
00:16:30.800 --> 00:16:32.760
Alright! That's our don!

225
00:16:32.760 --> 00:16:35.270
Drag him down!

226
00:16:33.680 --> 00:16:35.270
Get him!

227
00:16:39.440 --> 00:16:41.900
If I can get my arms
and legs out, I win!

228
00:16:42.610 --> 00:16:44.610
Why doesn't he falter?

229
00:16:46.400 --> 00:16:47.990
Why does he go that far?

230
00:16:47.990 --> 00:16:49.150
What?!

231
00:16:49.570 --> 00:16:51.530
This is gonna end it...

232
00:16:51.530 --> 00:16:53.490
for sure!

233
00:16:58.500 --> 00:17:01.540
Gum-Gum...

234
00:17:12.140 --> 00:17:13.510
Giant Hammer!

235
00:17:36.120 --> 00:17:37.540
Don Krieg...

236
00:17:37.540 --> 00:17:41.160
The don... The don
was defeated! How?!

237
00:17:41.160 --> 00:17:41.830
Dammit!

238
00:17:41.830 --> 00:17:43.380
Alright, Cabin Boy!

239
00:17:42.540 --> 00:17:45.790
Dammit! How? How was the don...

240
00:17:43.380 --> 00:17:45.790
Good job!

241
00:17:47.550 --> 00:17:48.920
He really did it!

242
00:17:48.920 --> 00:17:50.590
A-Amazing!

243
00:17:50.590 --> 00:17:51.970
Is this real?

244
00:17:51.970 --> 00:17:54.180
This is Don Krieg we're talking about!

245
00:17:54.180 --> 00:17:55.550
So strong!

246
00:17:55.550 --> 00:17:57.760
He's unstoppable!

247
00:17:58.890 --> 00:18:01.020
Wh-What's all the fuss?

248
00:18:01.020 --> 00:18:03.270
Oh! You've come to!

249
00:18:03.270 --> 00:18:04.650
He lost!

250
00:18:04.650 --> 00:18:06.020
Your don lost!

251
00:18:06.480 --> 00:18:07.480
What?!

252
00:18:23.290 --> 00:18:26.960
Quit your daydreaming
and save that kid already!

253
00:18:27.340 --> 00:18:28.420
Huh?

254
00:18:28.420 --> 00:18:30.260
He won't be floating back up!

255
00:18:30.260 --> 00:18:30.960
What?!

256
00:18:31.550 --> 00:18:34.640
Those with devil fruit
powers are hated by the sea.

257
00:18:34.640 --> 00:18:36.430
They sink like an anchor.

258
00:18:36.430 --> 00:18:38.600
What'd you say, you old fart?!

259
00:18:39.350 --> 00:18:41.060
You should've told me that sooner!

260
00:18:41.730 --> 00:18:43.890
What are you gonna do
if it's too late?!

261
00:19:14.550 --> 00:19:16.180
Hey! Hang in there!

262
00:19:16.800 --> 00:19:19.180
You said you wouldn't die, right?

263
00:19:20.060 --> 00:19:22.140
That's your conviction, right?!

264
00:19:22.770 --> 00:19:24.100
Right?!

265
00:19:27.440 --> 00:19:29.020
I won't die!

266
00:19:32.900 --> 00:19:35.950
I'm not gonna die here.

267
00:19:37.450 --> 00:19:39.030
Really, these guys...

268
00:19:42.870 --> 00:19:45.870
Zoro!

269
00:19:49.380 --> 00:19:52.380
Dying is worse than
giving up his ambition!

270
00:19:52.960 --> 00:19:54.380
The choice was easy!

271
00:19:54.380 --> 00:19:56.470
Just abandon your ambition!

272
00:20:06.230 --> 00:20:08.150
Every single one of them...

273
00:20:20.240 --> 00:20:23.450
I don't know why, but...

274
00:20:25.330 --> 00:20:27.830
if I withdraw even one step,

275
00:20:27.830 --> 00:20:34.090
it feels as if all the important oaths
and promises that I once made will shatter,

276
00:20:34.090 --> 00:20:37.470
and I won't be able to come
back to where I am now.

277
00:20:38.300 --> 00:20:42.760
Nobody stands a chance against
a spear of blind determination.

278
00:20:44.260 --> 00:20:50.730
I know an idiot who holds that
spear back for no good reason.

279
00:21:01.780 --> 00:21:03.240
Hey, Cabin Boy!

280
00:21:03.240 --> 00:21:05.240
Don't you die on me!

281
00:21:05.700 --> 00:21:07.950
Don! What's the matter?!

282
00:21:07.950 --> 00:21:11.120
Why was the don...?

283
00:21:10.250 --> 00:21:11.120
Don!

284
00:21:11.120 --> 00:21:13.500
Don Krieg has been defeated...

285
00:21:13.500 --> 00:21:15.750
That can't be true...

286
00:21:15.750 --> 00:21:18.340
He's the conqueror of the East Blue...

287
00:21:18.340 --> 00:21:20.340
Even if you say so...

288
00:21:20.340 --> 00:21:22.470
just take a look at him!

289
00:21:22.470 --> 00:21:26.560
His prized armor got shattered,
and he's out cold.

290
00:21:27.390 --> 00:21:29.980
He got beat good.
Don't you wanna see?

291
00:21:31.730 --> 00:21:35.230
He's the only man I ever admired...

292
00:21:35.230 --> 00:21:37.690
I thought no one could rival him!

293
00:21:44.870 --> 00:21:46.620
Hey wait, lackey!

294
00:21:46.620 --> 00:21:48.700
If you move, the poison will circulate!

295
00:21:48.700 --> 00:21:50.160
Sit still!

296
00:21:49.450 --> 00:21:51.160
I'm saying this for your own good!

297
00:21:50.160 --> 00:21:52.540
Hey! You're gonna die!

298
00:21:52.540 --> 00:21:53.920
Cabin Boy!

299
00:21:53.920 --> 00:21:55.460
Don't die!

300
00:21:55.460 --> 00:21:57.000
Can you hear me?!

301
00:21:57.000 --> 00:21:59.970
You still have things to do, right?!

302
00:22:00.470 --> 00:22:01.720
Cabin Boy! Don't die!

303
00:22:10.390 --> 00:22:11.640
You're such a...

304
00:22:13.900 --> 00:22:15.310
You're really something...

305
00:22:15.310 --> 00:22:17.900
I'm the strongest!

306
00:22:17.900 --> 00:22:20.570
I'll... I'll win!

307
00:22:20.570 --> 00:22:24.410
No one can surpass my power!

308
00:22:25.200 --> 00:22:26.490
Don! Please stop!

309
00:22:26.490 --> 00:22:29.040
Hold him down!
He's not even conscious!

310
00:22:30.120 --> 00:22:31.330
I'll win!

311
00:22:31.330 --> 00:22:33.250
Please stop, Don!

312
00:22:34.040 --> 00:22:36.710
I'll win with my own might!

313
00:22:44.800 --> 00:22:47.300
I...

314
00:22:47.300 --> 00:22:49.510
have to...

315
00:22:49.510 --> 00:22:51.220
win!

316
00:22:53.350 --> 00:22:55.810
Nobody can defeat me!

317
00:23:02.070 --> 00:23:03.570
Don Krieg...

318
00:23:03.570 --> 00:23:05.780
We lost.

319
00:23:06.200 --> 00:23:08.490
– Commander!
– Commander!

320
00:23:08.490 --> 00:23:12.000
Let's withdraw gracefully
and start anew.

321
00:23:14.790 --> 00:23:17.580
Thanks for everything, Sanji.

322
00:23:17.580 --> 00:23:18.750
Sure.

323
00:23:18.750 --> 00:23:20.460
Don't ever come back!

324
00:23:21.630 --> 00:23:23.050
Sanji,

325
00:23:23.050 --> 00:23:27.090
when he wakes up,
please tell him I said...

326
00:23:30.850 --> 00:23:34.600
"I'll see you again on the Grand Line."

327
00:23:35.690 --> 00:23:36.650
You...

328
00:23:37.480 --> 00:23:39.900
When I think about it carefully,

329
00:23:39.900 --> 00:23:43.110
that's the only thing I want to do...

330
00:23:43.690 --> 00:23:48.620
It seems that somewhere along the way,
Don Krieg's ambition became my own.

331
00:23:54.160 --> 00:23:55.620
I might...

332
00:23:56.160 --> 00:23:58.880
only have a few more
hours left in me...

333
00:23:59.580 --> 00:24:03.670
It's kinda stupid that I've resolved myself
without the time left to use it,

334
00:24:03.670 --> 00:24:06.260
but this time, I want to do
things on my own terms...

335
00:24:06.260 --> 00:24:07.380
in my own way...

336
00:24:08.010 --> 00:24:11.180
In that case, there'd be
nowhere for me to run, right?

337
00:24:17.890 --> 00:24:20.190
To hell with loyalty to the don.

338
00:24:20.730 --> 00:24:25.940
I've just been running,
using Don Krieg's name as a shield.

339
00:24:27.200 --> 00:24:32.830
Once you're resolved, you don't
have to think about worthless things

340
00:24:32.830 --> 00:24:35.580
like fearing your enemy,
or keeping yourself safe.

341
00:24:35.580 --> 00:24:37.910
He taught me that.

342
00:24:43.090 --> 00:24:44.300
Patty! Carne!

343
00:24:44.840 --> 00:24:46.800
Give him our grocery shopping boat!

344
00:24:46.800 --> 00:24:49.220
What?! Have you lost it?!

345
00:24:49.220 --> 00:24:52.470
Why do we have to give
our boat to pirates of all people?!

346
00:24:52.470 --> 00:24:55.850
What are we gonna use for
our grocery shopping?! You idiot!

347
00:24:55.850 --> 00:24:56.980
He's right!

348
00:24:56.980 --> 00:24:59.020
Let those guys swim!

349
00:24:59.020 --> 00:25:01.940
Just bring it out already!

350
00:25:05.570 --> 00:25:07.190
Okay, fine...

351
00:25:07.190 --> 00:25:08.950
Don't yell at us...

352
00:25:09.320 --> 00:25:12.530
– Okay, okay, we'll bring it out!
– Okay, okay, we'll bring it out!

353
00:25:20.290 --> 00:25:22.210
It's gonna sink!

354
00:25:35.720 --> 00:25:39.100
Why did I hesitate?
What was I so worried about?

355
00:25:39.100 --> 00:25:42.100
When I think back on it,
I feel like an idiot.

356
00:25:57.660 --> 00:25:58.750
Well, then!

357
00:25:59.120 --> 00:26:00.910
We gratefully accept the boat.

358
00:26:01.410 --> 00:26:03.750
We don't have to return it, right?

359
00:26:03.750 --> 00:26:04.580
Right.

360
00:26:05.000 --> 00:26:09.210
If you have the courage to return it,
you can go ahead and try, small fry.

361
00:26:09.210 --> 00:26:10.760
He's right!

362
00:26:10.760 --> 00:26:12.720
Just keep this in your brain:

363
00:26:12.720 --> 00:26:16.510
This is the Sea Restaurant,
the fighting, floating Baratie!

364
00:26:16.510 --> 00:26:17.470
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

365
00:26:18.720 --> 00:26:21.430
What a scary restaurant.

366
00:26:37.870 --> 00:26:44.730
As a kid, I had a dream of a dazzling treasure

367
00:26:44.930 --> 00:26:51.750
I had a map in my head that I knew would lead me

368
00:26:52.000 --> 00:26:58.850
Charted a course all on my own, so nobody would beat me

369
00:26:58.970 --> 00:27:06.110
The promised land was in my hand, drew a line in the sand

370
00:27:08.810 --> 00:27:11.490
Look where I am

371
00:27:13.720 --> 00:27:19.900
My one ambition's slipping right through my hands

372
00:27:20.240 --> 00:27:27.170
But if the world ever changes I'll call out your name

373
00:27:27.330 --> 00:27:34.250
We could return to a time when our lives were still the same

374
00:27:34.380 --> 00:27:41.380
Take me to the place where memories remain

375
00:27:41.480 --> 00:27:47.250
Please don't ever let them fade
